## Complete Control Allocation Record for OpenMRS

---

### Common Controls — Inherited from AWS

These controls are fully satisfied by AWS's implementation. MyClinic's responsibility is limited to obtaining and reviewing evidence of implementation (SOC 2 reports, AWS compliance documentation) and maintaining that evidence as part of the authorization package.

**Evidence requirement for all inherited controls:** Current AWS SOC 2 Type II report (available through AWS Artifact), reviewed annually by ISSO. Relevant control objectives noted in SSP for each inherited control family.

---

**Physical and Environmental Protection (PE) — Substantially Inherited**

| Control | Allocation | AWS Implementation | MyClinic Responsibility |
|---|---|---|---|
| PE-2 Physical Access Authorizations | Common — AWS | AWS controls physical access to data center facilities through badge systems, biometrics, and security personnel | Review SOC 2 annually; note control objective coverage |
| PE-3 Physical Access Control | Common — AWS | AWS implements layered physical access controls to server rooms; access logged and reviewed | Review SOC 2 annually |
| PE-6 Monitoring Physical Access | Common — AWS | AWS monitors physical access via CCTV and security operations | Review SOC 2 annually |
| PE-8 Visitor Access Records | Common — AWS | AWS maintains visitor access logs for data center facilities | Review SOC 2 annually |
| PE-12 Emergency Lighting | Common — AWS | AWS data centers implement emergency lighting systems | Review SOC 2 annually |
| PE-13 Fire Protection | Common — AWS | AWS implements fire detection and suppression systems | Review SOC 2 annually |
| PE-14 Environmental Controls | Common — AWS | AWS maintains temperature and humidity controls | Review SOC 2 annually |
| PE-15 Water Damage Protection | Common — AWS | AWS implements water damage protection | Review SOC 2 annually |

*Important exception:* Physical security of clinic workstations, the clinic building, and clinic facility access is entirely MyClinic's responsibility. The PE inheritance applies only to the AWS-hosted server infrastructure. Workstation physical security is a system-specific control documented in the endpoint security section.

---

**Maintenance (MA) — Physical Hardware Maintenance Inherited**

| Control | Allocation | AWS Implementation | MyClinic Responsibility |
|---|---|---|---|
| MA-2 Controlled Maintenance | Common — AWS (for infrastructure); System-Specific (for application) | AWS maintains physical servers, network hardware, and managed service infrastructure | MyClinic maintains OpenMRS application — patching, updates, configuration changes |
| MA-4 Nonlocal Maintenance | Common — AWS | AWS performs remote maintenance of infrastructure components under controlled conditions | MyClinic performs remote maintenance of OpenMRS application under documented change management procedures |

*Note on MA allocation:* The MA family illustrates why hybrid thinking is important. AWS handles physical hardware maintenance — MyClinic has no role in replacing a failed hard drive in an AWS data center. But application-level maintenance — OpenMRS version updates, dependency patching, configuration changes — is entirely MyClinic's responsibility. Both allocations need to be documented to prevent the assumption that AWS handles all maintenance.

